results.name: n with even digits (including zero) excluded.
link: Paul Tek, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: 2. Remove even digits (including zero) from each term.
example: The natural numbers with at least one odd digit in their decimal representation are: 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10, 11, 12, 13, ...
By excluding their even digits, we obtain: 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 1, 11, 1, 13, ...
results.author: _Dave Durgin_, May 22 2013
